icdasScore$score_id <-as.numeric(as.factor(icdasScore$name))

Cut off for the score

sumCutOff <- function(value, n, cutoff){
  sum(n[value >= cutoff & value < 90])
}



teethCutoffScore1 <- icdasScore1 %>% group_by(value) %>% summarise(n=sum(n)) %>%
summarise(cutoff_1=sumCutOff(value, n, 1)/sum(n)*100, 
          cutoff_2=sumCutOff(value, n, 2)/sum(n)*100,
          cutoff_3=sumCutOff(value, n, 3)/sum(n)*100,
          cutoff_4=sumCutOff(value, n, 4)/sum(n)*100,
          cutoff_5=sumCutOff(value, n, 5)/sum(n)*100
          )

knitr::kable(teethCutoffScore1, caption = "ICIDAS score 1 cutoff value above equal ")

cutoff_1 cutoff_2 cutoff_3 cutoff_4 cutoff_5
16.08665 13.99148 12.99716 5.646307 1.455966 
uniqueCutOff <- function(value, subject, cutoff){
  length(
    unique(
      subject[value >= cutoff & value < 90]
    )
  )
}

participantCutoffScore1 <- tibble(
c1=uniqueCutOff(icdasScore1$value, icdasScore1$participant_id, 1),
c2=uniqueCutOff(icdasScore1$value, icdasScore1$participant_id, 2),
c3=uniqueCutOff(icdasScore1$value, icdasScore1$participant_id, 3),
c4=uniqueCutOff(icdasScore1$value, icdasScore1$participant_id, 4),
)

Clustering

icdas1 <- rawSelection2 |> 
  select(starts_with("icdas_score_1"), "participant_id") |>
  pivot_longer(cols=starts_with("icdas_score_1")) |>
  group_by(participant_id, value) |>
  count() |>
  mutate(value=paste("icdas_score_1_val_", value)) |>
  pivot_wider(names_from = value, values_from = n, values_fill=0)

icdas2 <- rawSelection2 |> 
  select(starts_with("icdas_score_2"), "participant_id") |>
  pivot_longer(cols=starts_with("icdas_score_2")) |>
  group_by(participant_id, value) |>
  count() |>
  mutate(value=paste("icdas_score_2_val_", value)) |>
  pivot_wider(names_from = value, values_from = n, values_fill=0)


oneHotEncode <- function(df, cols){
  for (col in cols) {
    df <- df |> mutate(value=1) |> spread(col, value, fill = 0, sep ="_")
  }
  df
}
cdata <- rawSelection2 |>
  left_join(icdas1, by="participant_id") |>
  left_join(icdas2, by="participant_id") |>
  select(starts_with("icdas_score_1_val_"), 
         starts_with("icdas_score_2_val_"), 
         age,
         gender,
         sport,
         describe_health,
         "8s_pain",

         bars_after_training,

d <- dist(cdata,
method = "euclidean")
fit <- hclust(d, method="ward.D2")
plot(fit)
groups <- cutree(fit, k=4 )
rect.hclust(fit, k=4, border= 2:6)
abline(h = 4, col = "red")

ggplot(tibble(groups)) + geom_bar(aes(x=groups, fill="red")) + ggtitle("Number of participant per cluster")

rawSelectionGroups <- rawSelection2 %>% mutate(cluster=as.factor(groups))


p <- rawSelectionGroups %>% 
  mutate(last_dental_visit=as_factor(last_dental_visit)) |>     
  mutate(last_dental_visit=fct_relevel(last_dental_visit, 
                                       c("Within the past 6 months", 
                                         "6-12 months ago", 
                                         "1-2 years ago", 
                                         "More than 2 years ago")
                                       )) |> 
  ggplot() + 
  geom_bar(aes(x=last_dental_visit, y= ..prop.., col=cluster, fill=cluster, group=cluster), 
           position=position_dodge(), stat = "count")

p

ICIDAS by cluster

icdasScore1Cluster <- rawSelectionGroups %>% 
  select(starts_with("icdas_score_1"), "participant_id", cluster) %>%
  filter(! is.na(participant_id)) %>%
  pivot_longer(cols = starts_with("icdas_sco")) %>% 
  group_by(participant_id, cluster, value) %>%
  count()

# todo cross check the geom_bar
ggplot(icdasScore1Cluster) + geom_bar(aes(x=value, y=n), stat = "identity") +
facet_wrap(cluster~.,scales="free_x", ncol = 2)  

icdasScore1Cluster %>% group_by(cluster, value) %>% summarise(n=sum(n), distinct_subject=n_distinct(participant_id))
